-- Factbox: Key facts about Palm Inc
-- 
-- Tue Apr 13, 2010 4:27pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/04/13/us-palm-fb-idUSTRE63C3H220100413

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Palm Inc, the money-losing smartphone maker, has hired bankers to explore several options, including a sale of the company, whose smartphones sales have suffered badly against rivals like the iPhone and Blackberry. 

 Here are some facts about Palm Inc based on 2009 figures: PALM INC: Headquarters: Sunnyvale, Calif. Market capitalization: $870 million Revenue: $735 million Employees: 939 Smartphone units shipped: 2.4 million Key Products: Palm Pre Plus, Palm Pixi Plus, Operating System webOS: Rivals: Apple Inc Research in Motion Microsoft Corp Google Inc Nokia Oy Samsung Important Dates * 1992 - Company founded * 1997 - Became a part of 3Com * 1998 - Founders left to form a rival, Handspring * 2000 - Company's initial public offering * 2003 - Palm buys Handspring, maker of the Treo Phone * 2007 - Elevation Partners buys 25 percent stake in Palm * 2007 - iPod innovator Jon Rubinstein joins as Chairman * 2009 - Jan: Pre phone, and WebOs introduced at Consumer Electronics Show * 2009 - June: Pre phone sales begin * 2009 - June: Rubinstein named Palm CEO Source: Reuters; Company reports (Writing by  Franklin Paul  in New York and Carl Bagh, Bangalore Editorial Reference Unit; Editing by  Derek Caney )